theorem Topology.closure_interior_iter_six_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior
      (closure (interior
        (closure (interior
          (closure (interior
            (closure (interior (A : Set X))))))))) =
      closure (interior A) := by
  -- First collapse the innermost five alternations of `closure` and `interior`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior
        (closure (interior
          (closure (interior
            (closure (interior (A : Set X)))))))) =
        closure (interior A) :=
    Topology.closure_interior_iter_five_eq (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Rewriting the goal with `h₁` reduces it to a single extra alternation,
  -- which can be removed by the basic idempotence lemma.
  simpa [h₁,
        Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_eq
          (X := X) (A := A)]

theorem Topology.isOpen_interior_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsOpen (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
  exact isOpen_interior
